body:
We want to additionally prompt users with a notification if there is a warning about internal configuration. The message can include a link, so I added simple parsing for a URL to make it clickable.

~~I was originally going to change this for running too but I need some help finding where that text is parsed. If this is a good approach for test and run, then I'll make a separate change for app run/debug.~~

comment_data.body: nit: add methods should add something to a list. generateHtmlFragmentWithHrefTags.

in general, having code that throws a bunch of exceptions in its normal operation is annoying. Is there a method you can call to check whether a token is a valid URL without trying and catching? If there is not and this is used sparingly, fine to leave as is as IntelliJ already throws tons of exceptions.
nit: add test with multiple links.

Matching on this string could have false positives. Fyi @jwren.
We should consider making the string for bazel configuration warnings more unique and we need to document that this prefix needs to match the bazel tools.
An alternative to this design would be to display all bazel warnings in the g3 dart plugin. That would also allow showing the warning even before you run an app.

Is there a way to read configuration from flutter.json from within g3, or have flutter.json return a variable from elsewhere in g3? 

Using the g3 dart plugin would be nice too. This maybe wouldn't need to be specific to actions like run/test and would just detect whether the setup is running on mac without remote Dart. 

For now I think I'll just add a todo item. I wanted a message to appear for tools run on the command line as well.
We could use an apache validator instead? It would require importing a new library to our plugin. Otherwise I think this is okay since it's only triggered when the prefix is found.
There's one example of this on line 16; let me know if you're thinking of something else though.
lets file a bug along with the todo.

commit.message: Add notification for test if config warning
Change utility fn name and add TODO
Show notification for run as well
Read config warning directly and move test check
